title: Most charges dropped against former Rand Paul super-PAC aide
text:
Most charges dropped against former R... Most charges dropped against former Rand Paul super-PAC aide Next Story Prev Story 13 hrs ago Read more: The Hill 
A federal judge tossed out four of the five criminal charges against a former Rand Paul campaign aide Friday afternoon and all of the charges against a second. Judge John Jarvey from the Southern District of Iowa threw out four counts against Jesse Benton and John Tate, two longtime Paul family aides. Start the conversation, or Read more at The Hill.
